    {
      "step_id": "a3e10575",
      "step_index": 7,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 5) VERIFICATION / CHECKS (contradictions, alternatives, uncertainty)\n- **Could it be non-blocking?** If the amine pKa is unexpectedly low (less protonated) *or* if the polar imide-like ring drives overall logD low enough to limit membrane access to the intracellular cavity, hERG activity could drop.  \n- **Counterpoint:** the molecule still has substantial aromatic surface area and a tertiary amine; many compounds with similar polarity still show measurable hERG inhibition.\n- **Net:** the presence of the canonical **cation + two aromatics + flexible linker** outweighs the polarity-mitigating features, so \u201clikely blocker\u201d remains the best call.",
